{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:07:10.743829+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: a5fdd9aae5397f3dc7758fd6763bb801c801db73)", "id": "lc_e287897d-aabe-4ec0-97a5-a5757dfb342d"}, {"type": "text", "text": "from typing import Type\n\nfrom sqlalchemy import Column, String\n\nfrom app.base import Base\n\n\nclass User(Base):\n    \"\"\"\n    Model for user; used for auth and all.\n    \"\"\"\n    email = Column(String(255), unique=True, index=True, nullable=False)\n\n    @classmethod\n    def to_dict(cls, instance: Type[Base]):\n        \"\"\"\n        Additional functionality to convert a User instance into a dictionary\n        so it can be used as keyword arguments\n        \"\"\"\n        result = {}\n\n        for column in instance.__table__.columns:\n            result[column.name] = str(getattr(instance, column.name))\n\n        return result", "id": "lc_25bc3dd4-1b0d-47c1-8e7c-07b62533a0bc"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "03814ca0-5f55-4f91-98a9-e84784cf29fb", "tool_call_id": "call_01_QI6RpKkHOYbFtPxTSaH74376", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:07:10.814216+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 3a90a2babae1b84a1c81529908822a0ee1586612)", "id": "lc_158808ed-0047-407d-b21e-bc8916503c10"}, {"type": "text", "text": "from typing import Type\n\nfrom sqlalchemy.orm import Session\n\nfrom .base import Base\n\n\nclass BaseService:\n    \"\"\"\n    Base class for services. Handles DB initialization and saving a model\n    \"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, db: Session) -> None:\n        self.db = db\n\n    def save(self, model: Type[Base]) -> None:\n        self.db.add(model)\n        self.db.commit()\n        self.db.refresh(model)", "id": "lc_f45d70bc-4123-4613-94d5-6eb86e0571ef"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "e6a8ff8e-9f77-4c4b-b258-805837b86cd7", "tool_call_id": "call_00_KvcSYxeboiQ9mGWalUWS5022", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:07:19.065954+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here is the complete dependency and service stack for this FastAPI template:\n\n---\n\n## Main Python Dependency\n**FastAPI** (with the `[all]` extras bundle), served via **Uvicorn** (ASGI server).\n\n---\n\n## Service Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|---|---|\n| **Web framework** | FastAPI (with `fastapi.security.OAuth2PasswordBearer`) |\n| **ASGI server** | Uvicorn |\n| **Database** | **PostgreSQL** |\n| **SQL toolkit / ORM** | SQLAlchemy (Core + ORM via `sessionmaker`) |\n| **Async DB access** | `databases` library (with `[postgresql]` extras) + `asyncpg` |\n| **Sync DB driver** | `psycopg2` |\n| **DB migrations** | Alembic |\n| **DB utilities** | `sqlalchemy-utils` (for `database_exists` / `create_database`) |\n| **Redis** | `aioredis` (async Redis client) |\n| **Auth – JWT** | `python-jose` (with `[cryptography]` extras), algorithm **HS256** |\n| **Auth – password hashing** | `passlib` (with `[bcrypt]` extras), using `CryptContext(schemes=[\"bcrypt\"])` |\n| **Auth – token scheme** | FastAPI's `OAuth2PasswordBearer` (token URL: `/api/v1/user/login`) |\n| **File uploads** | `python-multipart` |\n| **Testing** | `pytest` |\n| **Container orchestration** | Docker Compose (3 services: `web`, `postgres`, `redis`) |\n\n---\n\n## Key Details\n\n- **Database URL pattern**: `postgresql+psycopg2://{user}:{password}@{host}:{port}/{db}`\n- **Redis**: configured via `REDIS_HOST` / `REDIS_PORT` env vars (defaults: `localhost` / `6379`), with `aioredis` as the Python client.\n- **JWT**: access token expiry = 30 minutes; refresh token expiry = 365 days; algorithm = HS256.\n- **Password hashing**: bcrypt via passlib's `CryptContext`.\n- **Base service pattern**: `BaseService` class wraps a SQLAlchemy `Session` and provides a generic `save()` method (add/commit/refresh). The auth `UserService` extends it.\n- **Python version**: 3.9 (specified in Pipfile).", "addition